                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/43</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-14T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1915, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Trevino informed the First Chief to-day that the Villista Generals Jose
                    Rodriguez and Carlos Amaya were apprehended yesterday at Pearson and shot last
                    night. A reward in gold is offered for the perpetrators of the Santa Ysabel
                    outrage. The sternest measures will be taken against all Villistas, who are all
                    considered bandits and outlaws.</p>
                <p>It is again requested that the military and immigration authorities cooperate by
                    denying refuge in the United States to these outlaws.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
